# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Mr. Chartist — Options Terminal | Environment Variables
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# ⚡ QUICK START: Just run `npm run dev` — no env vars needed!
#    The app works with TradingView + NSE data out of the box.
#    Add Dhan credentials below for premium real-time data.
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── DHAN BROKER API (Recommended — Primary Data Source) ──
# Sign up at https://dhan.co and create an API app at https://dhanhq.co/docs/v2/
# Dhan provides: Real-time Option Chain, Greeks, WebSocket Live Ticks
#
# DHAN_CLIENT_ID=your_dhan_client_id
# DHAN_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_dhan_access_token

# ── PROXY SERVER PORT (Optional) ──
# Default: 4002. Change only if port 4002 is already in use.
# PROXY_PORT=4002

# ── VITE PROXY URL (Optional) ──
# Default: http://localhost:4002. Change only for custom proxy setups.
# VITE_PROXY_URL=http://localhost:4002
